<glossary>
<definition id="fs-idm429505296">
<term>sensitivity analysis</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm443777344">what will happen if sales price, units sold, variable cost per unit, or fixed costs change</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-idm241691680">
<term>target pricing</term>
<meaning id="fs-idm251010112">process in which a company uses market analysis and production information to determine the maximum price customers are willing to pay for a good or service in addition to the markup percentage</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
